# silverman-blog-linkedin

## Canonical context (read first)

- [docs/CURRENT-STATE.md](docs/CURRENT-STATE.md) — implemented / validated / manual / deferred
- [docs/CONTEXT-AUTHORITY.md](docs/CONTEXT-AUTHORITY.md) — authority hierarchy and conflict rules
- [docs/GLOSSARY.md](docs/GLOSSARY.md) — Flow A completion layers, handoff vs publication

## Purpose

HTTP worker for blog-to-LinkedIn automation. n8n orchestrates over HTTP only; worker owns file I/O, validation, generation, metadata, and lifecycle moves. Business context: Solutions Architect positioning for senior remote roles and long-term technical leadership recognition.

## Critical guardrails

- **n8n → worker HTTP only** — never n8n Execute Command (ADR-0001)
- **OpenSpec before code** — no application changes without an approved change
- **No secrets** in HTTP responses or docs
- **Qualified Flow A language** — never bare "Flow A complete"; see GLOSSARY completion layers (`flow_a_complete` = campaign lifecycle only)
- **Blog handoff ≠ site published/live**; **LinkedIn implemented ≠ API validated**; **n8n imported ≠ unattended**
- **Develop on Mac**; **deploy Docker** on `192.168.0.194` (`/data/silverman-blog-linkedin`)

## Worker scope (summary)

Endpoints span health, Flow A (publish/package/schedule/calendar), LinkedIn publication (guarded), and draft generation. See CURRENT-STATE and `openspec/specs/` — not a Phase 1-only `/health` → `process-file` ladder.

## Editorial rules

Blog post is canonical (ADR-0002). LinkedIn posts are distribution assets. English, senior, practical tone. Dairector out of scope. Folder layout: `blog-posts/{ready,queued,processed,error}/`, `linkedin-posts/{review,approved,published}/`, `metadata/{runs,campaigns,backups}/`, `prompts/`.

